<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<RECIPES>
  <RECIPE>
    <NAME>Island Optimized West Coast IPA</NAME>
    <VERSION>1</VERSION>
    <TYPE>All Grain</TYPE>
    <BREWER>Charles Toepfer</BREWER>
    <BATCH_SIZE>60.567</BATCH_SIZE>
    <BOIL_SIZE>75.708</BOIL_SIZE>
    <BOIL_TIME>60.0</BOIL_TIME>
    <EFFICIENCY>75.0</EFFICIENCY>
    <OG>1.060</OG>
    <FG>1.010</FG>
    <IBU>65.0</IBU>
    <EST_COLOR>6.0</EST_COLOR>
    <ABV>6.5</ABV>
    <CARBONATION>2.50</CARBONATION>
    <PRIMARY_AGE>14</PRIMARY_AGE>
    <PRIMARY_TEMP>19.0</PRIMARY_TEMP>
    <NOTES>
A bright, clean West Coast IPA optimised for island water (low mineral, slightly alkaline).
Water profile is adjusted with gypsum and lactic acid to bring sulfate up and pH down into
the ideal mash range. Dry-hop addition is split — first charge at day 3, second at day 7 —
to maximise aromatic complexity without extracting harsh vegetal notes.

Target: crisp bitterness, pine and citrus aroma, straw-gold clarity, dry finish.
    </NOTES>

    <STYLE>
      <NAME>American IPA</NAME>
      <VERSION>1</VERSION>
      <STYLE_GUIDE>BJCP 2021</STYLE_GUIDE>
      <CATEGORY>India Pale Ale</CATEGORY>
      <STYLE_LETTER>A</STYLE_LETTER>
      <OG_MIN>1.056</OG_MIN>
      <OG_MAX>1.070</OG_MAX>
      <FG_MIN>1.008</FG_MIN>
      <FG_MAX>1.014</FG_MAX>
      <IBU_MIN>40</IBU_MIN>
      <IBU_MAX>70</IBU_MAX>
      <COLOR_MIN>6</COLOR_MIN>
      <COLOR_MAX>14</COLOR_MAX>
      <ABV_MIN>5.5</ABV_MIN>
      <ABV_MAX>7.5</ABV_MAX>
    </STYLE>

    <FERMENTABLES>
